@node DOCZEGO "Short overview"

	@{b}HfMounterMUI@{ub} is a "virtual floppies" manager. These floppies are emulated on a hard disk by "fmsdisk.device". HFMounter gives you a comfortable GUI to install, format and remove virtual floppies in the system.

@{b}A few words...@{ub}

	I've got "fmsdisk.device" for some time and use it willingly. The possibility of having many speedy "floppy drives" is often very useful (espacially for DMS archive depacking).

	I used @{b}HfMounter v2.2 @{ub}by Dirk Hebisch. But it wasn't exactly that, what I wanted. The main disadvantage were hardcoded paths to files. But there was no other similar program and I just used this one.

	I wrote a short Cli script attached to ToolManager. This script was removing mounted HFx: devices from the system. It wasn't comfortable. Then I got @{B}HFRemove @{UB}by Jens Weyer. Yes, work with "fmsdisk.device" became easier. But why should I use two programs? I wanted to have one doing all the things. My friend (Hi Kilu! :) ask me one day why don't I write such a program. That's the way HFMounterMUI was born... 

@endnode

@node OPIS "Detailed description of the program"

After program start you can see three pages in the window:

@{fg highlight} Program @{fg text}
        Buttons named "Hf0" to "Hf11" are placed here. If you press any of them you will be asked for desired action. You have four choices:

@{b}Mount@{ub}
You can mount choosen device without loosing previous data on it.

@{b}Format@{ub}
Device is mounted then formatted. You can set format parameters (filesystem, dir cache etc.) below.

@{b}Dismount@{ub}
Program tries to remove the device from the system and its icon from the Workbench.

@{b}Cancel@{ub}
Just no operation to do.

There are "Format" command options in the "Options" frame below.

@{fg highlight} Dismount @{fg text}
	You can see a list of currently mounted devices here and three buttons:

@{b} Rescan @{ub}
Program updates and refreshes the list of mounted HF devices.

@{b} Remove @{ub}
Dismounts selected unit.

@{b} Remove All @{ub}
Dismounts all mounted units.

You can doubleclick on any mounted device on the list to see information window.

@{fg highlight} Prefs @{fg text}
You can choose HF-Mountlist file here, also you can save the preferences on a disk (format settings are saved too).

@endnode

@node WYMAGANIA "Hard & soft requirements"

-  MUI 3.0 or newer.

-  'Mount' and 'Assign' commands in C:

-  'Format' command in 'Sys:System/' directory.

-  HF-Mountlist file (you can have it anywhere)

-  'fmsdisk.device' of course ;-)

@endnode

@node BYKI "Any bugs?"

I haven't found. Contact me if you find any.

@endnode

